The paper proposes a deep learning methodology for stroke lesion segmentation using multimodal MRI, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of diffusion and perfusion MRI modalities, which are related to neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
